-- Itochu, Kajima, Sumitomo to Buy Mazda Shares From Ford, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-11-16T17:11:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/ford-to-sell-mazda-shares-to-itochu-sumitomo-nikkei-reports.html
Itochu Corp., Kajima Corp. and
Sumitomo Corp. are among about 10 companies that have agreed to
buy Mazda Motor Corp. shares from Ford Motor Co., Nikkei English
News said, without citing anyone.   Itochu and Sumitomo each plan to purchase a 3 percent Mazda
stake from Ford for about 10 billion yen ($120 million),
according to the report. Ford may continue to hold a 3 percent
Mazda stake, Nikkei said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  